<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Engine Electrical - Removal - Sensor
        Wiring Harness
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="Svcproc1101" graphiccount="18">
        <title>Sensor Wiring Harness</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, disconnect
                    the main negative battery terminal before removing or installing any electrical components.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To avoid engine damage, make sure the key is in the OFF position before unplugging the connector
                    or relay for the ECM, IDM, and EGR drive module. Failure to turn the key to the OFF position will
                    cause a voltage spike and damage the electrical components.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To avoid engine damage, do not tug on any wiring harnesses while trying to remove them. If
                    resistance is felt, find the source of resistance and free up any connectors or clips that are
                    caught before proceeding.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2651113" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh09/h09021.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Disconnecting the VGT harness</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the wiring harness from the VGT actuator.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651114" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH09/H09012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Disconnecting the CMP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the wiring harness connector from the CMP sensor.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651115" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH09/H09018.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Disconnecting the ECT sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the wiring harness connector from the ECT sensor.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651116" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH09/H09011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Disconnecting the EBP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the wiring harness connector from the EBP sensor.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651117" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh09/h09027.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Disconnecting the EGR control valve connector</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the wiring harness connector from the EGR control valve.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651118" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH09/H09015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Disconnecting the EOT sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the wiring harness connector from the EOT sensor.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651119" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH09/H09014.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Disconnecting the MAP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the wiring harness connector from the MAP sensor.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651120" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH09/H09013.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Disconnecting the MAT sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the wiring harness connector from the MAT sensor.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651121" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH11/H11014.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Disconnecting the IPR valve connector</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect wiring harness connector from the IPR valve.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651122" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH09/H09017.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Disconnecting the EOP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the wiring harness connector from the EOP sensor.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651123" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH05/H05012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Disconnecting the block heater</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the block heater cable (optional).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651124" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH09/H09022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Disconnecting the fuel heater connector</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the wiring harness connector from the fuel heater (optional).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651125" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH11/H11015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Disconnecting the fuel pressure sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the wiring harness connector from the fuel pressure sensor (optional).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651126" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh11/h11022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Disconnecting the WIF sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the wiring harness connector from the WIF sensor.</para>
            <figure id="f2651127" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH09/H09016.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Disconnecting the CKP sensor</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the wiring harness connector from the CKP sensor.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect two additional, three wire connectors for the BCP sensor connector and brake
                shutoff valve connector to the valve cover gasket (optional).
            </para>
            <figure id="f2651128" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH09/H09052.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"/>
                <caption>BCP, Brake shutoff valve, and injector locations</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Injector connector (6)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">BCP sensor connector (optional)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Brake shutoff connector (optional)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect one, three wire ICP connector from valve cover gasket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect wiring harness at EGR drive module.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect one IDM connector. This is the one of three IDM connectors in the most forward
                position on the IDM.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect two ECM engine connectors. These are the two connectors towards the rear of the
                ECM.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651129" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH09/H09050.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>12 wire engine connector</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect one, 12 wire engine connector.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651130" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH09/H09051.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Intake air heater relay connectors (2)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Injector shield ground nut</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Top relay connector</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bottom relay connector</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect two intake air heater relay connectors.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove injector shield ground nut.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the sensor harness by disconnecting harness at the various tie down locations.</para>
        </step1>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>If removing complete harness; sensor and injector harnesses, continue with injector harness
                    removal before attempting to remove the sensor harness.
                </para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
    </svcproc>
